    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_ad.00221_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Camden NJ</name>
                    <date when="1890-11-28">Nov: 28 '90</date>
                </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Ed:</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>It is pretty sad days just now for me here&#8212;our dear brother Jeff<ptr target="n4995"/>
                died last Tuesday at St. Louis, Missouri, of typhoid pneumonia. Jessie<ptr target="loc.04763_n3"/>
                went on first train soon as she heard he was sick, but poor Jeff was dead
                when she arrived&#8212;George<ptr target="n0700"/> has gone on&#8212;(must have got there this morning)</p>
                <p>Hannah<ptr target="n0285"/> is poorly at Burlington Vermont, but gets about the house.</p>
                <p>Very cold here. I am still about not much about for I can only move by
                help, but have the grip badly, &amp; bladder trouble. I often think of you &amp;
                hope you have comfortable times&#8212;I have heard you have a good kind
                attendant who has been there some time in the asylum&#8212;I wish he would
                stop here at 328 Mickle Street &amp; see me a few minutes when he is in Camden.
                My best respects to Mr<ptr target="uva.00608_n1"/> and Mrs. Currie<ptr target="uva.00608_n1b"/>&#8212;</p>
            <closer> 
                <salute>My love to you</salute>
                <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_ad.00222_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
